<br>
First of all, I don't mind helping new people..If you send me a tell and your a &quot;true&quot; newbie..I'd prolly come pick you up and take you to the zone where you died and help you get back to your corpse, or toss you a crystalline shroud if i happen to have one, handy that i picked up while farming velium in Crystal Caverns while working on my Blessed Coldain Prayer Shawl quest.<br>
<br>
However the problem, that seems to be infecting all new people is, &quot;Your barking up the wrong tree.&quot; <br>
<br>
Make no mistake when I say this...I don't, won't and never will have some &quot;spare shaman gear&quot; hanging around in my bank...why not? cause i ain't no fuckin shaman<br>
<br>
if you are new and starting out.../who all 65 wizard is not gonna do a damn thing for you unless you need a ride to your body. if you looking for gear to help you out in the lower levels you need to be typing /who all 60 65 shaman you'll prolly have better luck with them.<br>
<br>
One thing I wanna mention right off the bat, for all you smartasses out there...don't try to be cute and log on tonight and make level 1 wizards and send me tells asking for cash or the phat lewts and think its gonna be cute...cause it won't<br>
<br>
and if you log on and make level 1 shamans, keep your swear filter on, cause i'm liable to be spreading some hate.<br>
<br>
A little common sense goes a long way...think before you speak. see it rhymes, kinda catchy...maybe you can hang on to it.<br>
<br>
I'm not applying for Saint Peters job either....I'm not heading up the &quot;Save the Newbies Foundation of Norrath&quot; I aint the president, hell i'm not even a member. But I don't mind helping the occasional new person out if your in a jam.<br>
